--- title: Coffee preferences author: Hannah, Orlando and Grace date: today # The following are optional but recommended warning: false image: tb.png format: html: code-fold: true code-summary: "Show code" code-tools: true --- ## Introduction We are investigating the relationship between coffee preferences and age, specifically preferred coffee style, amount consumed, coffee expertise and overall favourite coffee type from the tasing. The dataset we are using comes from a Great American Coffee Taste Test, during which thousands of people simultaneously blind-tasted the same four coffees. ::: {#80a221eb .cell execution_count=1} ``` {.python .cell-code} import seaborn as sns import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import numpy as np import pandas as pd ``` ::: # Investigating the Relationship Between Age and Coffee Bitterness ::: {#9da8062e .cell execution_count=2} ``` {.python .cell-code} import seaborn as sns import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import numpy as np import pandas as pd df = pd.read_csv("../../data_sources/coffee_survey.csv") sns.catplot(data = df, x = "coffee_a_bitterness", y = "age", kind = "bar") df = df[df["coffee_a_bitterness"] != "Missing"] ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](ProjectCoffee_files/figure-html/cell-3-output-1.png){width=487 height=470} ::: ::: Pie chart, distribution of coffee styles ::: {#f78f6b5b .cell execution_count=3} ``` {.python .cell-code} style_counts = df["style"].value_counts() plt.pie(style_counts, labels=style_counts.index, autopct="%1.1f%%", startangle=140) plt.axis("equal") plt.title("Distribution of Coffee Styles") plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](ProjectCoffee_files/figure-html/cell-4-output-1.png){width=540 height=409} ::: ::: # Investigating the Relationship Between Age and Amount of Coffee Consumed ::: {#10af3ca9 .cell execution_count=4} ``` {.python .cell-code} import seaborn as sns import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import numpy as np import pandas as pd import plotly.express as px custom_order = ['<18 years old', '18-24 years old', '25-34 years old', '35-44 years old', '45-54 years old', '55-64 years old', '>65 years old'] df["age"] = pd.Categorical(df["age"], categories=custom_order, ordered=True) custom_order = ['Less than 1', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'More than 4'] df["cups"] = pd.Categorical(df["cups"], categories=custom_order, ordered=True) fig = sns.displot(data = df, x = "age", hue_order = ['<18 years old', '18-24 years old', '25-34 years old', '35-44 years old', '45-54 years old', '55-64 years old', '>65 years old'], binwidth = 1, hue = "age", col = "cups") axs = fig.axes[0] for ax in axs: ax.tick_params(axis="x", rotation=30) figu = px.bar(df, x="age", y="cups", color="cups", barmode="group", category_orders={"age":['<18 years old', '18-24 years old', '25-34 years old', '35-44 years old', '45-54 years old', '55-64 years old', '>65 years old'],"cups":['Less than 1', '1', '2', '3', '4', 'More than 4']}, pattern_shape="cups", pattern_shape_sequence=[".", "x", "+", "-", "/","|"]) figu.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](ProjectCoffee_files/figure-html/cell-5-output-2.png){width=3031 height=521} ::: ::: # Investigating the Relationship Between Expertise and Coffee Preference ::: {#d2a247e1 .cell execution_count=5} ``` {.python .cell-code} import seaborn as sns import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import numpy as np import pandas as pd custom_order = ['Coffee A', 'Coffee B', 'Coffee C', 'Coffee D'] df["prefer_overall"] = pd.Categorical(df["prefer_overall"], categories = custom_order, ordered = True) sns.catplot(data = df, x = "prefer_overall", y = "expertise", kind = "bar") plt.xlabel("Coffee Preference") plt.ylabel("Expertise") plt.title("Coffee Preference and Expertise") plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](ProjectCoffee_files/figure-html/cell-6-output-1.png){width=488 height=490} ::: :::
